          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_hhXcCi": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Wear & care"
          }
        },
        "text_KYQ8qF": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The Core / Spark is splash resistant (IP65). It can withstand light rain and minor water splashes, such as when washing your hands. However, it is not designed to withstand heavy rain, showers, or full water immersion.</p><p>The Core / Spark contains strong magnets that may interfere with certain medical devices. For more information, please refer to the <strong>Safety & Regulatory Information</strong> section at the end of this manual.</p><h4>Tip</h4><p>Do not store your Core / Spark for extended periods (more than 3 months) with a fully depleted battery, as this may result in permanent battery damage.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_P6NyaD": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Battery maintenance guide",
            "answer": "<p>When not in use, the battery in your wearable will slowly discharge. If the device remains unused for an extended period (for example, 3 months or longer), the battery may become over-discharged. This can cause permanent damage to the battery’s internal components. In severe cases, the battery and the device may no longer function. This behavior is common to all modern lithium batteries.</p><p>To prevent this, charge and discharge your wearable at least once every three months to maintain battery health. If you use your device regularly, such as at least once per week, no additional precautions are necessary.</p><h4>What happens if the battery is permanently damaged?</h4><p>Currently, the battery in our wearables cannot be replaced. This is due to the use of adhesives to improve water resistance. Opening the device may damage internal mechanical components, preventing reassembly.</p><p>We aim to make batteries replaceable in future products. However, achieving this in a compact and tightly integrated form factor presents significant engineering challenges.</p><p>For this reason, it is especially important to take proper care of your wearable’s battery.</p><p>If you suspect that your device’s battery has been damaged, please contact our support team. We will do our best to assist you: <a href=\"/pages/contact-us\">contact support</a></p>"
          }
        },
        "text_ecFNQA": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Silicone strap & body strap</strong></p><p>Both straps are highly durable and suitable for use in all environmental conditions.</p><p><strong>Leather straps</strong></p><p>We use premium-quality leather. Natural variations in color and markings, such as scars or wrinkles, are inherent characteristics of genuine leather and contribute to its unique appearance.</p><p>Over time, the leather will naturally conform to your wrist and develop a distinctive patina. To preserve its quality and longevity, we recommend minimizing exposure to moisture.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_ExTXVE": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_YbafmG": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Lock system for the rig (Core only)"
          }
        },
        "text_HgaFMq": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>To remove the Core from its rig, twist it counterclockwise and take it off.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_WAHFyi": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_3.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_mfDFqP": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>To attach the Core to the rig, hold it slightly above the rig and release it. The Core will magnetically snap into place.</p><p>When placing the Core on the rig, ensure that the buttons face toward your hand. If you prefer to wear the Core on your other wrist, you can adjust the screen orientation in the mobile app.</p><h4>Tip</h4><p>Make sure you both hear and feel the spring-loaded pin engage when the Core locks into place on the rig. This confirms that it is securely attached and prevents it from falling off.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_dn4KAP": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_k7g7gq": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Changing the watch straps"
          }
        },
        "text_NytJdp": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>To change the watch strap, turn the device over and release the two rivets located on each side.</p><p>We offer a range of strap options for the Soundbrenner Core and Spark, crafted from high-quality materials such as silicone, woven nylon, and leather. Explore the latest collection at:</p>"
          }
        },
