        "subheading_4FUbLa": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Tracking on Core / Spark"
          }
        },
        "text_TLzjQj": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>In the <strong>Track</strong> app, set the duration of your practice session and select the instrument you will be using.</p><p>To modify the list of instruments available on your device, open the mobile app and navigate to:</p><p><strong>Settings → User Profile → Instruments</strong></p><p>To begin your session, tap the soundwave icon twice quickly.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_FfyzYr": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_12.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_6R9XD8": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>If you have already been practicing but did not start the session on your device, you can adjust the start time. Press the bottom button and rotate the wheel to set the correct start time.</p><p>When a practice session is active, the <strong>Track</strong> app will automatically open each time you wake the screen for quick access. The LED ring gradually fills with orange to indicate progress toward your goal.</p><p>To disable the orange tracking light, open the mobile app and turn it off in the Core / Spark settings.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_NyDj7h": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_13.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_Wph8pr": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>During an active session, tap the soundwave icon twice quickly to pause or end the session.</p><p>When editing a session, you can delete it or adjust the start and end times.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_bc3Uzm": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_3gJNCt": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Tracking with our mobile app"
          }
        },
        "text_nT77Fi": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>When you track a practice session on your device or in the mobile app, any changes you make, such as adjusting your goal, instrument, or start time, will automatically sync between both devices. All saved sessions are also synchronized automatically.</p><p>If you experience synchronization issues, you can initiate a manual sync in the mobile app under your device’s settings.</p><p>The mobile app provides several ways to view and analyze your practice data, including a practice calendar, streak tracking, and additional insights.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_t9EaiU": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_14.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_U7NDz9": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "heading_3eNxUU": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Vibrating metronome"
          }
        },
        "subheading_zTfCrT": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Body strap"
          }
        },
        "text_3VGXjf": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Where you position the Core / Spark on your body can significantly affect your experience. The optimal placement varies from musician to musician.</p><p>Using the included body strap and body strap rig, you can wear the Core on your wrist, arm, or ankle. With the included extension piece, you can also attach it to your chest, shoulder, or thigh.</p><h4>Tip</h4><p>During your first few sessions, experiment with different positions to determine what feels most comfortable and effective. Wearing the device on your chest typically provides the strongest and most precise vibration feedback.</p><p>Ensure that the strap is secured firmly. A tighter fit enhances the transmission of vibrations and improves the overall experience.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_chjewp": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_15_cde650db-62d3-4d7c-a550-eb0337acf687.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_rgUPrz": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>If you have thin arms or ankles</strong></p><p>To set the body strap to its smallest setting, align the arms of the rig with the markings on the strap as shown in the illustration below.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_E3Fych": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_16.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_3w6Xgd": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_t9TDDQ": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How to feel the beat"
          }
        },
        "text_3WUEWG": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Using a vibrational metronome is a different experience from using a traditional audible metronome. When you first begin using the Core / Spark, allow yourself time to adapt. Do not be discouraged if it feels unfamiliar at first, as this is a normal part of the learning process.</p><p>With continued use, the vibration can become a subconscious cue that supports your sense of timing and helps you maintain the beat naturally.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_fjemp8": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_NydDnh": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Setting up a rhythm"
          }
        },
        "text_pitfrD": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>1. Press the bottom button to select the first value.</p><p>2. While selected, use the wheel to change the value.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_FV98pp": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_17.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_9XNnh4": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>3. Press the bottom button again to edit the next value. Press the top button to go back.<br/></p><p>4. Tap the soundwave twice quickly to start or pause the metronome.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_ViiDii": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_18_06d82c4b-0518-4e7c-b95a-d1c241c9824e.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_TqbGXK": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h4>Tip</h4><p>You can also start the metronome by pressing and holding the bottom button. The metronome will begin as soon as you release the button.</p><p>This method allows you to precisely align the start of the metronome with the rhythm of the music or audio you are listening to.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_GzhHqt": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_nxFYxr": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Change LED lights, vibrations & sounds"
          }
        },
        "text_PPf9Mq": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Because every musician has different preferences, you can customize your Core / Spark using the mobile app.</p><p><strong>LED lights & vibrations</strong></p><p>To adjust or disable the LED lights and vibrations, open the mobile app and navigate to:</p><p><strong>Settings → Select your Core → Metronome vibrations</strong> or <strong>Metronome lights</strong></p><p>We recommend experimenting with different vibration intensities and durations to find the settings that work best for you.</p><p><strong>Sounds</strong></p><p>To customize or disable the metronome sounds, open the mobile app and go to:</p><p><strong>Settings → App settings → Metronome sounds</strong></p>"
          }
        },
        "image_ppDgRj": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_19.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_kGcVqV": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_7pAhzQ": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Multi-player sync"
          }
        },
        "text_fE43Up": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The Core / Spark can be synchronized with other Soundbrenner wearables by connecting all devices to the same mobile device. You can sync up to five devices simultaneously, allowing everyone to feel the beat together.</p><p>Core / Spark can only maintain one active connection at a time. If you want to switch to a different mobile device, first unpair or disconnect it from the current device. To access the unpairing prompt, open the <strong>Settings</strong> app on your Core / Spark, navigate to <strong>Bluetooth</strong>, and press the bottom button.</p><p>Once the device is ready to pair, open the Soundbrenner app on the new mobile device. Then navigate to:</p><p><strong>Settings → Add a Soundbrenner wearable</strong></p><p>Select the wearable you would like to connect and follow the on-screen instructions.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_wWCNAW": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_20.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_circle_fifths": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "heading_circle_fifths": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Circle of fifths"
          }
        },
        "subheading_circle_fifths_intro": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Using the circle on Core 2 / Spark"
          }
        },
        "text_circle_fifths_intro": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The <strong>Circle of fifths</strong> is a music theory tool that shows how keys, chords, and scales relate to each other. Neighboring keys on the circle share nearly all of the same notes, which is why they often sound natural together.</p><p>On Core 2 / Spark, the feature gives you a quick reference while practicing, composing, or learning a song.</p>"
          }
        },
        "subheading_circle_fifths_screen": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Read the screen"
          }
        },
        "text_circle_fifths_screen": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The top of the screen shows related chords from the current area of the circle. Major chords appear on the top row and minor chords appear below them. The currently selected key is marked with a small rectangle.</p><p>The lower part of the screen shows the notes in the selected scale. For example, C major shows C D E F G A B C, while A minor shows A B C D E F G A.</p>"
          }
        },
        "subheading_circle_fifths_controls": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Navigate the circle"
          }
        },
        "text_circle_fifths_controls": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Rotate the wheel to move left or right around the circle. Moving clockwise follows fifths and adds sharps to the key signature. Moving counter-clockwise follows flats.</p><p>Press the bottom button to switch the focus between the major and minor rows.</p><h4>Tip</h4><p>Use nearby chords as a starting point when writing progressions. They are closely related to the selected key and usually feel cohesive together.</p>"
          }
        },
        "subheading_circle_fifths_enharmonic": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "F♯ and G♭"
          }
        },
        "text_circle_fifths_enharmonic": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>At the bottom of the circle, F♯ and G♭ share the same position. They sound the same but are written differently, which is called an enharmonic equivalent.</p><p>Core 2 / Spark shows F♯ when you arrive from the sharp side and G♭ when you arrive from the flat side. A dotted line marks this transition.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_XNKXfy": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "heading_kFjpNR": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Chromatic tuner"
          }
        },
        "subheading_bE3ihU": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Microphone tuner (Core 2 / Spark only)"
          }
        },
        "text_r7gJrb": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Open the <strong>Microphone tuner</strong> app and play a note. The device will detect the closest pitch and display its deviation in cents. As you adjust the pitch, the LED ring will change from red to green to indicate when the note is in tune.</p><p>To adjust the tuning reference (A4), press the bottom button and rotate the wheel to set your preferred frequency (default: 440 Hz).</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_D7bYPy": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_21.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_pgRMDY": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_tTkj9B": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Contact tuner"
          }
        },
        "text_hfkATY": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The original Core includes the <strong>Contact tuner</strong> app pre-installed.</p><p>For Core 2 / Spark, a magnetic tuning accessory is required to use the <strong>Contact tuner</strong> app. You can choose between a tuning clip or adhesive tuning mounts. Each accessory includes a unique code to unlock the Contact Tuner app on Core 2 / Spark.</p><p>Contact tuning is designed for use with guitar, bass guitar, ukulele, and violin.</p><h4>Tip</h4><p>To purchase magnetic tuning accessories, visit:</p>"
          }
        },
        "button_BtwNMt": {
          "type": "button",
          "settings": {
            "label": "Soundbrenner shop",
            "button_size": "large",
            "icon_position": "none",
            "link": "shopify://collections/all"
          }
        },
        "text_awM8te": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Attaching a magnetic tuner mount</strong></p><p>Each magnetic tuner mount comes with pre-applied adhesive. Remove the protective backing and firmly attach the mount to the headstock of your instrument.</p><p>The tuner mount is designed for long-term use, so you do not need to remove it after each session. If you decide to remove it, peel it off carefully to avoid damaging the surface of your instrument.</p><p><strong>Using the contact tuner</strong></p><ol><li>Open the <strong>Contact tuner</strong> app on your device.</li><li>Remove the wearable from its rig by twisting it counterclockwise.</li><li>Attach the magnetic port on the side of the device to the tuner mount or tuning clip.</li></ol><p>When you play a string, the LED ring and display will activate to show the tuning information.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_4Q8cPB": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_22_5f68ba56-6f3a-406a-8b21-c81f076897ed.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_UDGGpU": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "heading_DqMpQN": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Decibel meter"
          }
        },
        "text_BGtakD": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Sound levels</strong></p><p>Open the <strong>Decibel meter</strong> app to measure current, average, and maximum sound levels. The Core / Spark measures sound levels above 70 dB and uses A-weighting for its readings.</p><h4>Tip (Core only)</h4><p>For improved accuracy, remove the Core from its rig and place it on a soft surface, such as a cloth or your hand, before opening the <strong>Decibel meter</strong> app.</p><p><strong>Volume alarm</strong></p><p>Your Core / Spark monitors sound exposure throughout the day and alerts you when volume levels reach potentially harmful thresholds, based on World Health Organization guidelines:</p><ul><li>80 dB: 5 hours 30 minutes per day</li><li>85 dB: 1 hour 45 minutes per day</li><li>90 dB: 30 minutes per day</li><li>95 dB: 10 minutes per day</li></ul><p>Your privacy is important to us. No audio is recorded or stored at any time.</p><p>To disable the volume alarm and all background sound measurements, open the mobile app and navigate to:</p><p><strong>Settings → Select your device → Volume alarm</strong></p>"
          }
        },
        "image_fbRE9a": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_23.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_NC9YAa": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "heading_w4TnW9": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Smartwatch"
          }
        },
        "subheading_nPMqjm": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Smartphone notifications"
          }
        },
        "text_U3HEgD": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Smartphone notifications are supported on both iOS and Android devices. Your Core / Spark will mirror the notifications you receive on your mobile device and is compatible with all apps. At this time, it is not possible to enable or disable notifications for individual apps independently from your mobile device settings.</p><p>For notifications to work reliably, your wearable must be connected through the Soundbrenner app, not just visible in your phone's Bluetooth settings.</p><p>To receive notifications, iOS and Android require certain permissions. When you connect your device to the Soundbrenner app for the first time, these permissions will be requested automatically during setup.</p><p>On Android, make sure notification access and background activity are enabled. On iPhone, make sure notification permissions are granted and Bluetooth remains enabled.</p><p>If you are not receiving notifications after completing the setup process, please refer to the troubleshooting section below:</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_f3A3i8": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Core smartphone notifications troubleshooting",
            "answer": "<p>For the device to receive notifications reliably, it must be connected through the Soundbrenner app, not just visible in your phone's Bluetooth settings.</p><p>If the wearable appears in Bluetooth settings but notifications still do not work, remove or forget it there first, then reconnect it from inside the app.</p><p>If you are unable to receive notifications after setup, follow the steps below.</p><p><strong>If you are using an iOS device</strong></p><p>Your iPhone must grant the Core / Spark permission to receive notifications.</p><ol><li>Open the <strong>Settings</strong> app on iOS (outside the Soundbrenner app).</li><li>Go to <strong>Bluetooth</strong>.</li><li>Tap the <strong>(i)</strong> icon next to your device.</li><li>Enable <strong>Share System Notifications</strong>.</li></ol><p>If notifications still do not appear, review the <strong>Show Previews</strong> setting:</p><ol><li>Open the <strong>Settings</strong> app on iOS.</li><li>Go to <strong>Notifications → Show Previews</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Always</strong> or <strong>When Unlocked</strong>.</li></ol><p>If <strong>Never</strong> is selected, notifications will not be forwarded to your device.</p><p>Note that this setting can also be configured individually per app. To check this:</p><ol><li>Go to <strong>Settings → Notifications</strong>.</li><li>Scroll down and select the relevant app.</li><li>Tap <strong>Show Previews</strong> and ensure it is set to <strong>Always</strong> or <strong>When Unlocked</strong>.</li></ol><p><strong>If you are using an Android device</strong></p><p>First, ensure you have the latest version of the Soundbrenner app installed from Google Play (version 1.23.0 or later). To check, open the app's page in Google Play and see whether an update is available.</p><p>Next, confirm that the Soundbrenner app has permission to:</p><ol><li>Access your notifications.</li><li>Access <strong>Nearby devices</strong>.</li><li>Access <strong>Location</strong> if required by your Android version.</li><li>Run without battery optimization or background restrictions.</li></ol><p>To verify permissions:</p><ol><li>Open the Soundbrenner app.</li><li>Navigate to <strong>Settings → Select your Core → Smartwatch</strong>.</li></ol><p>If there is no warning displayed below the <strong>Smartphone Notifications</strong> switch, your permissions are correctly configured. If a warning appears, follow the on-screen instructions to grant the required permissions.</p><p><strong>Additional troubleshooting (iOS & Android)</strong></p><ol><li>Ensure your Core is running the latest firmware version. To check, go in our mobile app to <strong>Settings → Core / Spark settings → Firmware update</strong>.</li><li>On your Core, open the <strong>Settings</strong> app and confirm that <strong>Smartphone Notifications</strong> is enabled.</li><li>The Core can only receive notifications from the mobile device it was originally unlocked with. This protects your privacy during multi-device sync sessions. If notifications still do not work despite all permissions being enabled, perform a factory reset and set up the device again using the account you are currently logged into.</li><li>If you are still unable to get notifications to work, please <a href=\"/pages/contact-us\">contact us</a>. We're looking forward to helping you out.</li></ol>"
          }
        },
        "text_X9Jggx": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Reading notifications</strong></p><p>New notifications automatically appear on the Core / Spark when you wake the screen.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_pWEwmn": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_24.jpg"
          }
        },
        "subheading_7C6VdM": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Manage notifications"
          }
        },
        "text_rAXGi4": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<ul><li>Rotate the wheel to scroll through the text of a notification.</li><li>Press the bottom button to delete the current notification and display the next one in the queue. The number in the top-right corner indicates how many notifications are currently queued.</li><li>Press and hold the bottom button to delete all notifications in the queue.</li><li>Press the top button to send all queued notifications to the Notification Center (up to a maximum of 20).</li><li>To access the Notification Center, rotate the wheel to the right while on the watch face.</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "image_JwgLWG": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_25.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_nVhP36": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Phone calls</strong></p><p>When you receive a phone call, the Core / Spark will vibrate and display the option to accept or decline the call.</p><p>As the Core / Spark does not have a built-in speaker or microphone, you will need to use your phone or connected Bluetooth headphones to conduct the call.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_BmnLkM": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_zztz43": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Smartphone music remote (Core 2 / Spark only)"
          }
        },
        "text_XgaEYF": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Control any media playing on your mobile device, including music, videos, podcasts, and audiobooks. This feature is compatible with all apps, such as Apple Music, Spotify, and YouTube.</p><p>On Android devices, the Soundbrenner app requires access to your notifications to enable this feature.</p><p>1. Rotate the wheel to the left to access the <strong>Smartphone music remote</strong>.</p><p>2. Tap the soundwave icon twice quickly to start or pause playback.</p><p></p>"
          }
        },
        "image_iEpim6": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_26_703c7e0f-16c0-4c43-889c-f2c711c1f354.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_p6RUM9": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>3. Press the bottom button to select the current media playing. Twist the wheel forward for next, backward for previous.</p><p>4. Press the bottom button again to select the volume. Twist the wheel forward to increase, backward to decrease.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_ctxrVb": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_27_dd1a31de-13a4-4584-a847-b8f8d38fe4c9.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_yGiD6W": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_qcM8GX": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Timer"
          }
        },
        "text_8awQtz": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Press the bottom button to select whether you want to adjust the hours, minutes, or seconds. Once selected, rotate the wheel to set the desired time.</p><p>Tap the soundwave icon twice quickly to start or pause the timer.</p>"
          }
        },
        "subheading_wqcpNK": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Stopwatch"
          }
        },
        "text_rfGpyy": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Tap the soundwave twice quickly to start or pause the stopwatch.</p>"
          }
        },
        "subheading_3rT9jG": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Alarm"
          }
        },
        "text_hdLRXH": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>To create an alarm, rotate the wheel to select <strong>New alarm</strong>, then press the bottom button to confirm.</p><p>Use the wheel to set the desired time. Press the bottom button to select the days on which the alarm should be active. Rotate the wheel to the right to enable a specific day. Active days are indicated by an underline. If no days are underlined, the alarm is active every day by default.</p><p>To change the alarm status, select <strong>On</strong> using the bottom button. Rotate the wheel to choose <strong>Off</strong> or <strong>Delete</strong>, then press the bottom button to confirm your selection.</p>"
          }
        },
        "subheading_8T3AUg": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Settings"
          }
        },
        "text_DcDGni": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Airplane mode</strong></p><p>Disables all wireless communication, including Bluetooth. When Airplane Mode is enabled, the device cannot connect to your mobile device.</p><p><strong>Bluetooth</strong></p><p>Displays the current connection status. Press the bottom button to unpair the device and make it available for pairing again.</p><p><strong>Factory reset</strong></p><p>Erases all data and preferences and restores the Core / Spark to its factory settings. After a factory reset, the device will be locked until setup is completed again using the Soundbrenner app.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_G4W7PG": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "heading_8JzcNh": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Troubleshooting"
          }
        },
        "subheading_LiwjxQ": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Connecting to your mobile device"
          }
        },
        "text_bR3bMT": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>If your Core, Core 2, or Spark does not connect to your mobile device, try the steps below.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_97qzHE": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Connection troubleshooting",
            "answer": "<p>Try these steps in order:</p><ul><li><strong>Make sure your wearable is powered on:</strong> Charge it first if needed.</li><li><strong>Core / Spark can only actively connect to one mobile device at a time:</strong> If you are switching phones or tablets, disconnect or unpair it from the previous device first.</li><li><strong>Pair inside the Soundbrenner app:</strong> Do not pair from your phone's Bluetooth settings first. In the app, go to <strong>Settings → Add a Soundbrenner wearable</strong>.</li><li><strong>If the BPM stays at 120, vibration does not respond, or app controls do not affect the wearable:</strong> It is usually not connected correctly in the app. Remove any existing Bluetooth pairing from your phone settings, then reconnect it from inside the Soundbrenner app.</li><li><strong>Unpair on the wearable:</strong> On the wearable, open <strong>Settings → Bluetooth</strong> and press the bottom button twice to remove old pairings.</li><li><strong>Restart your mobile device:</strong> This often clears stuck Bluetooth state.</li></ul><p><strong>If you use Android</strong></p><ul><li>Remove the device in the Soundbrenner app. Then go to <strong>Android settings → Connected devices</strong>, open your wearable, and tap <strong>Forget</strong>.</li><li>Make sure <strong>Bluetooth</strong> is enabled.</li><li>Check app permissions in <strong>Android settings → Apps → Soundbrenner → Permissions</strong>. Allow <strong>Nearby devices</strong>. For <strong>Location</strong>, choose <strong>Allow all the time</strong> if available. Otherwise choose <strong>Allow only while using the app</strong>.</li><li>Set <strong>Android settings → Apps → Soundbrenner → Battery</strong> to <strong>Unrestricted</strong> and allow background activity if your phone has a separate background restriction setting.</li><li>If your phone has many connected Bluetooth devices, remove any you do not need temporarily.</li></ul><p><strong>If you use iPhone</strong></p><ul><li>Remove the device in the Soundbrenner app. Then go to <strong>iPhone settings → Bluetooth</strong>, tap <strong>(i)</strong> next to your wearable, and choose <strong>Forget This Device</strong>.</li></ul><p>If your device still does not connect, please <a href=\"/pages/contact-us\">contact our support team</a>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "subheading_qTRhUi": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Soft restart"
          }
        },
        "text_6mCaUq": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>If your device behaves unexpectedly, press and hold both buttons for 5 seconds, and continue holding them until Recovery Mode appears.</p><p>Use the bottom button to select <strong>Restart</strong> and perform a soft restart.</p><p>If the device remains unresponsive, perform a hard restart.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_L8yyXG": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_28_774d1249-6672-45a8-a36f-916890b9c4cf.jpg"
          }
        },
        "subheading_D9MaqY": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Hard restart"
          }
        },
        "text_nGgRmi": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>This procedure should only be used if your Core / Spark is unresponsive.</p><p>Ensure that the charging cable is connected to a power source. Attach the cable to the magnetic port on the device, then detach it. Immediately reattach the cable a second time to initiate the hard restart.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_7Wy3B7": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_2.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_89iXCF": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "heading_jbn8mk": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Compliance"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_YML4rP": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Safety",
            "answer": "<p>Warning: medical conditions</p><p>If you currently have a medical condition or have a history of medical conditions that may be affected by the Soundbrenner Core/Spark, consult with your physician before using the product. Medical conditions include (but are not limited to):</p><ul><li>White Knuckle Syndrome</li><li>Hand-Arm Vibration Syndrome</li><li>Blackouts</li><li>Epilepsy</li><li>Postural Hypertension</li><li>Allergic Reactions to Silicone</li><li>Any other heart, neurological, or skin conditions</li></ul><p>Warning: medical device interference</p><p>If you use any medical device that may be affected by the Soundbrenner Core/Spark, consult with your physician before using the product. Medical devices include (but are not limited to):</p><ul><li>Coronary Stents</li><li>Defibrillators</li><li>Pacemakers</li><li>Any other implanted medical device</li></ul><p>Stop using the Soundbrenner Core/Spark if you suspect that it is interfering with your medical device or if you experience any discomfort.</p><p>Warning: frequent and prolonged usage</p><p>Frequent and prolonged use of the Soundbrenner Core/Spark may cause skin irritation in some users. If you experience itchiness, redness, and/or swelling while using the Soundbrenner Core/Spark, remove the device immediately and stop using it until your skin returns to normal. Consult your doctor should any of the symptoms persist.</p><p>Caution: electrical equipment</p><p>Your Soundbrenner Core/Spark and its charging cable are electrical devices and should be handled with care. Never use your device in extremely low or high temperatures.</p><p>Substances in this product and battery may harm the environment or cause injury if handled or disposed of improperly.</p><p>Remove your Soundbrenner Core/Spark if it feels warm or hot.</p><p>Caution: magnets</p><p>The Soundbrenner Core/Spark and the charging cable contain magnets. All credit cards, key cards, and any other object containing a magnetic stripe should be stowed safely away from those products.</p><p>Caution: batteries</p><p>Use only an authorized Soundbrenner charging cable to charge your device to avoid any safety or electrical hazards.</p><p>Do not attempt to change the battery on your own. This will void the warranty and could cause injury.</p><p>Always disconnect the charging cable from the electrical socket as soon as your device is fully charged.</p><p>Never charge your device when moisture is present.</p><p>Never put your device or charging cable near any inflammable or explosive materials.</p><p>Caution: water</p><p>Even though your Soundbrenner Core/Spark is sweat proof and partially water-resistant, it should never be submerged in water under any circumstances.</p><p>Do not use your device in the rain or in wet environments for prolonged periods.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_Q6Gzia": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Warranty",
            "answer": "<p>Our warranty terms are available <a href=\"/pages/terms-of-warranty\" title=\"Terms of warranty\">here</a>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_x6nkte": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Privacy policy",
            "answer": "<p>Our app's privacy policy is available <a href=\"/pages/privacy-policy-the-metronome-app\" title=\"Privacy policy The Metronome app\">here</a>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_jEVqLT": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Terms of service",
            "answer": "<p>Our app's terms of service are available <a href=\"/pages/terms-of-service-the-metronome-app\" title=\"Terms of service The Metronome app\">here</a>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_ebWN9y": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Recycling",
            "answer": "<p>Dispose of this product at an appropriate electronics recycling center to support sustainable reuse and resource conservation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_9qnJwy": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "EU declaration",
            "answer": "<p>Soundbrenner Limited hereby declares that this product complies with the essential requirements and all relevant provisions of Directive 1995/5/EC.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_cBk3Ra": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "FCC compliance",
            "answer": "<p>The product complies with part 15 of the FCC rules. Operation is subject to the following two conditions: They may not cause harmful interference. They must accept any interference received, including interference that may cause undesired operation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "heading_xRAPtb": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "FAQs"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_6gYW4q": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How to charge the Core / Spark in the shortest time possible?",
            "answer": "<p>Core / Spark charges over standard 5V USB and needs up to 0.5A (500mA) to reach full charging speed.</p><p>Most USB power sources meet or exceed that requirement, including:</p><ul><li>Computer USB ports</li><li>Wall chargers</li><li>Portable battery packs</li></ul><p>In practice, almost any normal USB charger will charge Core / Spark at full speed.</p><p>It is also safe to use a charger with a higher current rating. The device will draw only the power it needs.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_QdNUrT": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How to update the firmware of Core / Spark?",
            "answer": "<p>Firmware updates are installed through the Soundbrenner app.</p><ol><li>Open the app and sign in to your account.</li><li>If needed, connect your Core / Spark in <strong>Settings → Add a Soundbrenner wearable</strong>.</li><li>Open your device settings.</li><li>Tap <strong>Firmware update</strong>.</li><li>Follow the on-screen instructions and keep your phone connected to the internet until the update finishes.</li></ol><p>If you do not see a firmware update option, your device is already up to date.</p><p>On iPhone, the device may unpair after the update. If that happens, pair it again through the Soundbrenner app.</p><p>If a firmware update does not complete successfully, the device may temporarily enter recovery mode. In most cases, this does not mean the device is defective. Keep the wearable charged, reopen the Soundbrenner app, and try the update again. If recovery mode does not clear after repeating the update flow, please <a href=\"/pages/contact-us\">contact our support team</a>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_YNVk4P": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How to improve the tuner sustain of Core?",
            "answer": "<p>If note detection is too short, try adjusting the angle of Core / Spark on the tuner mount.</p><p>A small position change can improve vibration pickup and make note detection longer and more stable, so you do not need to pluck or strum as often.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_ableton_sync": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do I sync Core / Spark with Ableton Live?",
            "answer": "<p>The usual setup is <strong>Ableton Live → the Soundbrenner app → Core / Spark</strong>.</p><p>Enable Ableton Link in Ableton Live and in the Soundbrenner app. Then connect your wearable in the app. Core / Spark does not normally connect directly to Ableton Live on its own.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_connection_symptoms": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why does my wearable stay at 120 BPM or not respond correctly?",
            "answer": "<p>If the BPM stays at 120, vibration does not respond, or app controls do not affect the wearable, it is usually not connected correctly in the app.</p><p>Remove or forget the wearable in your phone's Bluetooth settings if it appears there, then reconnect it from inside the Soundbrenner app.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
